{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> δείλη</b>, ἡ, <br /> <b>afternoon</b> (δ. ἡμέρας τελευτή [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Definitiones” 411b), ἔσσεται ἢ ἠὼς ἢ δείλη ἢ μέσον ἦμαρ 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.111 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: divided into <b>early</b> and <b>late</b> (πρωΐα and ὀψία), περὶ δείλην πρωΐην γενομένην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.6 (opposed to δ. ὀψίην, [prev. work] 9); δείλης ὀψίης [prev. author] 7.167, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 57.9; περὶ δείλην ἤδη ὀψίαν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.26; later περὶ δ. ἑσπέραν 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.533, 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 3.12.7. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> δ. alone, <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> <b>early afternoon,</b> δείλῃ δὲ τέμνεται ὀπώρα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 255; ἤδη ἦν μέσον ἡμέρας.., ἡνίκα δὲ δείλη ἐγένετο 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 1.8.8; ἀμφὶ δείλην [prev. work] 2.2.14 (opposed to ὀψέ, [prev. work] 16); περὶ δείλην 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.101, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.69, 103 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπὸ δείλης from <b>the hour of afternoon,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 564a19; τῆς δείλης \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<b>in the course of the afternoon,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 7.3.10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but also, <br /><Level4><b>__II.1.b</b></Level4> <b>late afternoon,</b> τῆς ἡμέρας ὅλης διῆλθον.. ἀλλὰ δείλης ἀφίκοντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 3.3.11; ἡνίκα ἦν δ., opposed to τῆς νυκτός, [prev. work] 3.4.34, compare 4.2.1, 7.2.16 \">Refs</a>]; μέχρι δείλης ἐξ ἑωθινοῦ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “HG” 1.1.5, compare 4.1.22; ἀπ᾽ ἠοῦς μέχρι δείλης 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Definitiones” 411a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἕωθεν καὶ δείλης early in the morning and <b>late in the evening,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Fragmenta” 531; πρὸς τὴν δείλην [prev. author] “HA” 596a23 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; δείλαν alone, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 10.5. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> in late Prose, <b>any time of day,</b> περὶ μεσημβρίαν δ. about mid-<b>day,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD(?): Achilles Tatius Astronomus 3.2. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.2.b</b></Level4> apparently, <b>day,</b> opposed to <b>night,</b> δείλ (η) ς ἐργ (άταις) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PLond.” 1.131r44 (2nd c.AD), compare 244. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G6788","accentedUnicode":"δείλη","shortDef":"afternoon; evening","mediumDef":"afternoon; evening","stepGloss":"afternoon","stepTransliteration":"deilē","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}